track.name: If Heartaches Were Nickels
comments: He is distinguished from other musicians by bright style and very catchy compositions. He is undoubtedly belongs to those who can already be attributed to the great musician.
@chrisspix - your "keep the faith" tag looks familiar!
If you don't know ...that is the great Leslie West with Joe on this song
....just check him out with' anything' he does with Beth Hart, a fit, fine, blues singing woman who's done some time & come out a bit of a legend. Her & Joe really work....keep the faith all......

to the person, who wrote the description under the video - the Leslie West version is the same version recorded on Joe's debut. they did it together. Joe released it in 2000, West 5 years later, but it's the same one.
i get pink floyd tingles up and down my spine
...I'd have enough to spend all day at the car wash....
